Installing S3Host
*****************

   The provided Installer script @{b}Install_S3Host@{ub} will copy @{b}S3Host@{ub} and
it's online documentation onto your harddisk.

   You must install @{b}MUI@{ub} on your system before you can use @{b}S3Host@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "Using S3Host" "S3Host.guide/Using S3Host"
@Next "ARexx"
@Prev "Installing S3Host"
@Toc "Main"

Using S3Host
************

   Using @{b}S3Host@{ub} is quite simple.

  1. Configure the serial settings. Remember that 19200 bps is only
     supported on the S3a, not the S3.

  2. Start the terminal application on your S3 or S3a.  Be sure to set
     it to the same serial settings as S3Host.  Select @{b}Y-Modem-G@{ub} as the
     file transfer protocol.

  3. Set S3Host to @{b}Online@{ub}.

  4. Send files from the Amiga to the S3 by adding them to the send
     listview, or simply drop icons into the listview.  Start the
     transfer by selecting @{b}Receive@{ub} on the S3/S3a.

  5. Receive files from the S3 by first selecting the files with the S3
     terminal and then start the transfer by clicking on the @{b}Receive@{ub}
     gadget.  The @{b}Received Files@{ub} listview will show up with all files
     received.


   You may abort the transfer at any time by setting S3Host to @{b}Offline@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "ARexx" "S3Host.guide/ARexx"
@Next "Acknowledgments"
@Prev "Using S3Host"
@Toc "Main"

ARexx
*****

   S3Host features a ARexx port named "S3Host".  Some of the commands
take arguments, which are indicated as standard shell templates.

@{b}Quit@{ub}
     @{b}Quit@{ub} causes S3Host to terminate. This is a builtin MUI command.

@{b}Hide@{ub}
     @{b}Hide@{ub} causes S3Host to iconify. This is a builtin MUI command.

@{b}Show@{ub}
     @{b}Show@{ub} causes S3Host to deiconify. This is a builtin MUI command.

@{b}Help File/A@{ub}
     Writes a list of all ARexx commands support by S3Host to the file
     named @{i}File@{ui}.  This is a builtin MUI command.

@{b}Receive@{ub}
     @{b}Receive@{ub} forces S3Host to send a @{b}Receiver Ready@{ub} character ('G') to
     the S3/S3a. If Comms is about to send files, this will start the
     transfer.

@{b}Send Files/M/A@{ub}
     Puts the indicated files on the send list.  Sending will be
     started if the remote machine (i.e.  the S3/S3a) signals Receiver
     Ready.

     This command returns "0" if everything went ok, or "5" if one or
     more files don't exist.

@{b}Online@{ub}
     Forces S3Host to go online.

@{b}Offline@{ub}
     Forces S3Host to go offline. Any pending transfers will be
     aborted, and the serial driver is released.

@{b}IsOnline@{ub}
     Checks whether S3Host is currently online.  Returns "0" for
     offline and "1" for online.


@EndNode

